headline.main: Adolph S. Ochs Dead at 77; Publisher of Times Since 1896; Adolph S. Ochs Dies at 77; Times Publisher Since 1896

snippet: CHATTANOOGA, Tenn., April 8. -- Adolph S. Ochs, publisher of THE NEW YORK TIMES, died here at 4:10 o'clock this afternoon amid the scenes of his first venture in publishing and of his first professional triumphs. He was 77 years old.

byline.original: Special to THE NEW YORK TIMES
